  "texts": [
    "H Bayesian Validation of Judge Error RatesTo validate the findings against measurement error, the observed disclosure rates are corrected using the Rogan and Gladen [34] estimator.",
    "While this formula provides a point estimate, accurately propagating the uncertainty of the judge's error rates is a known statistical challenge.",
    "Frequentist solutions, such as Lang and Reiczigel [19], derive complex adjustments to the standard formula to achieve nominal confidence interval coverage.",
    "Full Bayesian approaches, like Flor et al. [13], build unified MCMC models that treat the true prevalence itself as a random variable with a prior.",
    "The method used here occupies a methodological middle ground: modeling the judge's error rates All key findings remain statistically significant (95% credible intervals exclude zero for differences) and substantively meaningful after uncertainty propagation (Table 4)."
  ],
